<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.001 G 29/10.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reports that the body of the King arrived at the Piraeus yesterday,
                            having been delayed one day on account of fog. There was an impressive
                            procession at Athens, the streets were lined with soldiers, while the
                            houses and sidewalks were crowded with spectators. A short service was
                            held at the cathedral in the presence of the Royal family, the Holy
                            Synod, the Cabinet, Diplomatic Corps and officials.</p>
                        <p>Thanks the President for his appointment as special representative.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>